Is there a way to configure Jira so that cancelling an issue creation sends back to the "Browse Project" page rather than to the "Dashboard" ?

User must choose a Project before creating an issue (at least user must choose the project in Step 1 of issue creation), so it would logical to sends back to the "Browse project" page..

Implementing programmatically the FieldLayoutScheme / FieldLayout, I have to describe wich field/customField visibilty and order.
To simplify it, created an Helper Class to assure the existing actions (hide, show, moveUp and moveDown) and too a new action "moveTo". (See Class extract below ...)

When moveTo(...) is executed, it failed due to an incoherence between the List [fieldLayoutItems] of EditableDefaultFieldLayoutImpl (FieldLayoutImpl) and the integer [position] of FieldLayoutItemImpl. When FieldLayoutItem.getPosition() reached the value 1, internalList.indexOf(fieldLayoutItem) is already to 0. Normally, the two values are supposed to identical (following the Javadoc !).

Note that the FieldLayoutItemImpl constructor make the correct test, but return an incorrect exception's message  ...
        if (position < 0) throw new RuntimeException("Field layout item cannot be less than 1");

Do I use correctly a correct way, or is there a real bug ?


